JOHANNESBURG - Tiger Brands could be facing a class-action lawsuit over one of the world’s worst food-borne disease outbreaks.
	
	A team of lawyers plans to file the case against the food giant on behalf of the victims’ families. Listeriosis has killed 183 people, with most of the deaths occurring in Gauteng. READ: Listeriosis claims three more lives A baby, less than a month old, is one of the latest victims. The Health Department traced the outbreak to Tiger Brands’ Enterprise factory in Polokwane. But Tiger Brands is refusing to take responsibility for the crisis, saying there’s no link between their products and the victims. eNCA